Sprint 1
--------

What went well/What we learned: We were able to get through the hurdle of setting up Docker containers and orchestrating them with docker-compose to have our microservices communicate with each other. Also, some teams were able to utilize best practices such as test-driven development early on. 

What didn’t go well: Communication can be difficult working in large groups working remotely, especially with pull requests into shared branches. User story tags are not helpful in helping to find relevant user stories. 

How we will improve: We will start the integration process (merging into dev) earlier to avoid last minute merging and confusion. We will utilize prefixes on our Taiga user stories to help group members find relevant tasks. Finally, we will delete task branches off of GitHub to keep the repository tidy.
